Bus Reservation in C language 
Overview
This Bus Reservation System is a console-based application developed in the C programming language. It facilitates the management of bus bookings, providing functions for reservation, cancellation, and display of available seats.
Features
Reservation: Users can reserve seats for a specified destination and date.

Cancellation: Allows users to cancel their existing reservations.

Seat Availability: Displays the current status of available and booked seats.

User-friendly Interface: The application provides a simple and intuitive interface for users to interact with.

Functions
1. Reserve Seat
This function handles the reservation process, allowing users to select a destination, date, and seat.
2. Cancel Reservation

void cancelReservation();
Enables users to cancel their existing reservations by providing their booking details.

3. Display Seat Availability

void displaySeats();
Displays the current status of seats, indicating which ones are available and booked.

4. Main Menu
int main();
The main function acts as the control center, presenting options to the user and calling relevant functions based on their choices.

5. Initialize Seats
void initializeSeats();
Sets up the initial state of seats, marking them as available for reservation.

6. Display Menu
void displayMenu();
Prints the menu options for users to choose from.

How to Use
Compile the source code using a C compiler.
Run the executable file.
Follow the on-screen prompts to navigate through the reservation system.
Note
This application is designed for educational purposes to demonstrate basic principles of programming in C.
Feel free to explore and modify the code to enhance its functionality or adapt it for specific needs.

